<h2>What Easy Read is</h2>
<p>Easy Read is a way to make important information easier to understand. It combines simple words, clear structure and meaningful pictures for people who prefer or need this format.</p>
<p>Start by identifying the audience and their information needs. Easy Read can help people with intellectual disability, cognitive disability or low literacy, as well as some people who are learning English.</p>
<p>This page contains the guidance needed to plan, write, design, publish and test Easy Read content. It includes page structure, writing and imagery guidance, downloadable formats and accessibility requirements.</p>

<h2>Easy Read as a method</h2>
<p>Easy Read is a content and design method supported by the Easy Read content block, About Easy Read callout and page templates. The image-and-text block is not the whole Easy Read feature.</p>
<p>Plan the message, write and define terms, select or create images, review the complete page and test it with people who use Easy Read. A page can use several content blocks, but each block should communicate one primary concept or action.</p>
<p>Use <code>nsw-easy-read-content</code> around a complete Easy Read page or an Easy Read section embedded in a standard page. The content block also works outside this wrapper with standard NSW Design System typography.</p>

<h3>Easy Read content block</h3>
<p>The content block pairs one primary concept or action with a meaningful image. It supports the method but does not make a page Easy Read by itself.</p>
